http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Ballari-swimmer-wins-laurels/article13994826.ece

City boy Uttej (12), who has hearing disabilities, has brought laurels to the district and State by winning a bronze in the open swimming competitions at the 20th National Games of the Deaf, organised by Telangana Sports Council in Hyderabad.Uttej, a student of the Government School for Deaf and Dumb here, has been undergoing coaching in swimming for a year under Rajani Lakka and had participated for the first time in the national-level event.“Uttej finished the 200 metres freestyle in 4.57.48 to clinch a bronze to make us happy,” Ms. Rajani told The Hindu .